def apply(self, other):
        if isinstance(other, datetime):
            # reset timezone and nanosecond
            other = datetime(
                other.year,
                other.month,
                other.day,
                other.hour,
                other.minute,
                other.second,
                other.microsecond,
            )
            
            # Define business hour duration
            business_hours_minutes = 8 * 60  # 8 hours
            
            # Example logic for adjusting the input datetime
            # Add 1 business day if the input is after business hours
            if other.hour >= 16:
                other += timedelta(days=1)
            
            # Round the input datetime to the next business day
            while other.weekday() > 4:  # Skip weekends
                other += timedelta(days=1)
            
            # Add business hours to the input datetime
            # This is just a basic example, the actual logic will depend on the specific business rules
            other += timedelta(minutes=business_hours_minutes)
            
            return other
        else:
            raise ApplyTypeError("Only know how to combine business hour with datetime")
